    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>\n                  OM-85 is a bacterial lysate from common respiratory tract pathogens, with an excellent safety profile, widely used to prevent recurrent respiratory tract infections. Several studies have been reporting the antiviral roles of OM-85. Here we demonstrated the effect of\n                  <jats:italic>ex-vivo</jats:italic>\n                  OM-85 exposure in nasopharyngeal cells collected from COVID-19 patients. OM-85 decreased the SARS-CoV-2 N1 gene expression and increased RIG-I (DDX58) gene expression in these cells. These data support the antiviral effect of OM-85 against SARS-CoV-2.\n                </jats:p>",
